This paper deals with algorithms for handling subsets of well quasi orderings (WQOs), which are commonly studied in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and logic (cs.LO). The use of filters and ideals is also a common technique in the study of partially ordered sets (cs.DS) and category theory (cs.CC). Finally, the development of generic or parameterized algorithms is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
